modules.description: This module processes unstructured text data according to RFC822 and RFC5322, handling elements like whitespace, line breaks, and invalid characters. It provides functions to parse strings into structured tokens, manipulate those tokens, and convert them to UTF-8 strings, with specific support for folding whitespace and comment removal. It is used for parsing email headers, HTTP headers, and similar formats where line folding and structured whitespace are required.

Parses raw byte sequences into structured values using a predefined format. It operates on `bytes` input and produces a structured type `Unstrctrd.t` through a parser combinator. This module is useful for deserializing binary data into a specific in-memory representation during data processing or network communication tasks.
